headline: An Exclusive Club Wants More Land for Birdies. Sorry, Owls.
abstract: The golf course in Jersey City, N.J., says it needs the land to compete for tournaments. A birder counters, “It’s really just an obscenity.”
lead_paragraph: JERSEY CITY, N.J. — The snowy owl was first spotted just beyond the 18th hole of one of the most expensive golf courses ever built.
keywords: Liberty National Golf Club (Jersey City, NJ)
